description:
Final pass: This was missed because reviewers focused on timing side-channels, not the correctness of multiple matches.

Root cause: The constant-time iteration at lines 519-528:
  if (ret == 0) {
      /* Signature verified - record but don't return yet. */
      if (found_idx < 0) {
          found_idx = (int)i;
          found_ret = 0;
      }
      continue;  // Continue checking remaining peers
  }

If multiple peers' public keys produce valid signatures for the same frame:
1. The first matching peer (lowest index) is recorded
2. Later matching peers are ignored

This could happen if:
- Two peers have the same Ed25519 keypair (configuration error)
- A cryptographic collision occurs (astronomically unlikely with Ed25519)

The comment at line 523 says 'record but don't return yet' - implying only one match is expected. But the code doesn't validate this assumption.

Impact: If two peers share a keypair, packets from either are attributed to the first one in peer_table. The last_seen timestamp is updated for the wrong peer, affecting LRU eviction decisions. Packets are delivered correctly but peer attribution is wrong.

Fix: Either:
1. Document that duplicate keypairs cause undefined peer attribution
2. Log a warning if multiple peers match
3. Reject frames with multiple matching signatures as ambiguous
